news.title: Bank of Maharashtra reduces home loan rates by 15bps
news.para: Bank of Maharashtra will offer home loans at 8.35% as against 8.5% earlier. The bank has also waived off its processing fee on home loans, a statement said.

news.title: Kerala government amends housing scheme guidelines for fisherfolk
news.para: The money will be granted to those beneficiaries who have their own land 200 metres outside the high-tide zone, but presently reside within 50 metres from the high-tide line.

news.title: Centre green-lights homes up to 250 sq meter in private forests of Goa & Uttarakhand
news.para: The clarification circular was issued after the advisory committee of the Union environment ministry deliberated over the concern that sales of small holdings in private forests are leading to fragmentation.

news.title: Tamil Nadu announces new property values for over three lakh roads, streets
news.para: In Chennai alone, the composite value for close to 1.5 lakh streets and roads has been announced. The highest being 28,500 per sqft in and around the Boat Club area. Registration charges are a flat 7% of the composite value.

news.title: Gurugram RWAs write to Haryana CM, want ban on four-floor buildings revoked
news.para: The associations also sought revoking of ban on stilt plus four floors citing loss to the plot owners who are unable to carry out construction despite buying plots at market rates.

news.title: Noida: Developers of stalled projects to be apprised of recalculated dues this week
news.para: If the builders accept the rehabilitation package, over one lakh homebuyers — 32,000 are in the Noida projects and 68,000 in the Greater Noida projects — will soon get ownership rights.

news.title: ED arrests Ornate Spaces' MD in money laundering case
news.para: Machindar proposed the Grove Tower on a plot as free sale in the market for developing buildings for UTI employees. He received a commencement certificate from MHADA authority.

news.title: ED opposes interim bail plea of Supertech's chairman in money laundering case
news.para: ​Arora's application was moved before Additional Sessions Judge Devender Kumar Jangala on account of his "deteriorating medical condition which has been aggravating ever since his incarceration as he was already suffering from various life-threatening diseases".

news.title: China lifts policy bank loans, raising housing support expectations
news.para: The People's Bank of China, which released the data in a statement on Tuesday, did not say how China Development Bank, Export-Import Bank of China and Agricultural Development Bank of China would use the loans.

news.title: BPTP acquires land in Gurugram for Rs 87 crore
news.para: According to the documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, the land has been acquired by Countrywide Promoters Pvt Ltd, a subsidiary of BPTP Group and it has paid Rs 6.1 crore as stamp duty for the transaction.

news.title: China developer CIFI proposes new restructuring terms to halve offshore debt
news.para: The debt revamp proposal, which also includes swapping part of the debt for equity, aims to halve the firm's debt to $3.3 billion to $4 billion, it said in a filing.

news.title: Adanis to fund Dharavi project via internal accruals, SPV stake sale
news.para: In a statement, the group, which has promised to invest Rs 21,000 crore in the project, said it roped in design firm Sasaki, consultancy firm Buro Happold as design planners for the project as well as some experts from Singapore Housing Development Board.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Plant to process C&D waste will come up in Gyaspur, not Gota
news.para: Just four months after allotting 23,000 sq m of land in Gota’s TP Scheme 56 for the plant, the standing committee has laid a resolution in its January 4 agenda to relocate the plant.

news.title: Nagpur civic body razes 15 pucca houses obstructing Gopal Nagar nullah
news.para: The NMC’s anti-encroachment squad had thrice attempted to raze illegal constructions in 2023 after local residents filed a petition at the Nagpur bench of Bombay High Court in 2020.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body razes Chandrasekharpur slum, frees two-acre government land
news.para: The BDA razed 350 asbestos rooms and three shops during the drive carried out with Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation (BMC).

news.title: Soon, no ground floor houses at Tambaram
news.para: Officials from the town planning department, who inspected flood-affected homes in December concluded that houses on the ground floor in Perungalathur, CTO Colony, Irumbuliyur, Varadharajapuram, Keelkatalai, Pammal, and Thiruneermalai were mostly inundated.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body all set to auction commercial properties to recover tax dues
news.para: The properties to be auctioned are those which the civic body has sealed and attached but property dues of which are still pending.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP razes six illegal colonies, frees 15-acre agriculture land
news.para: During the demolition, people gathered at the site and DTCP officials appealed to them that they should not invest their hard earned money in such unauthorised colonies and should contact the office of DTP for any enquiry before buying a land/plot.
